<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-08T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-08T10:00:00-05:00" n="448" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/14816:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-08T18:00:00+03:00">September 8, 1941—6
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 8—4:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1645. The Iranian Ambassador told me this afternoon that the Soviet
                                and British Governments have now requested the surrender to them of
                                the German agents in Iran rather than their mere expulsion and that
                                the Iranian Government in reply is suggesting that the women <pb facs="0467" n="459" xml:id="pg_459"/> and children be sent to
                                Germany via Turkey and that the men be placed in a concentration
                                camp in Iran under British supervision.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>